"n.独白；个人长篇演说 【英】 n. 独白(soliloquy)；个人长篇演说(a prolonged discourse) 【考】 opera : aria / play : monologue(独唱曲是一个人在歌 剧中唱/独白是一个人 在戏剧中说) 【记】 mono(单个)+logue(说 话)→一个人说话 n. 独白; 独脚戏 【记】mono单独, logue说话－一个人说话－独白 【参】monomania(n 偏执狂); mania(n 狂热); monopolize(v 独佔) 【类】opera: aria = play: monologue独唱曲是一个人在歌剧中唱 = 独白是一个人在戏剧中说 【记】mono + logue monologue (n.)  1660s, ""long speech by one person,"" from French monologue, from Late Greek monologos ""speaking alone,"" from Greek monos ""single, alone"" (see mono-) + logos ""speech, word,"" from legein ""to speak"" (see lecture (n.))."
